      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Organometallic reagents such as sodium acetylide undergo an addition reaction with ketones, giving alcohols:</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ0VUIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--fa81b83ebd318d3bf4298eaa616e8cee94096963/OChem_09_EC_038.jpg\" alt=\"Acetone reacts in the presence of sodium acetylide and hydronium ion to form an alcohol.\">\n<p>How might you use this reaction to prepare 2-methyl-1,3-butadiene, the starting material used in the manufacture of synthetic rubber?</p>",
